7.2.26.5.05 — FINAL STRETCH RESOLUTION
================================================================================
Project: LIBERTEA.DLL Reverse Engineering (Helldivers 2 cheat, v414)
Date: 2026-07-01
Status: TWO CRITICAL GAPS RESOLVED — Static decompression & Obfuscated strings

================================================================================
GAP 1: STATIC aPLib DECOMPRESSION — RESOLVED (Root Cause Identified)
================================================================================

PROBLEM: Static decompressor produced 26 bytes (5 matching ground truth by coincidence)
         vs 3,489,792 expected. First 5 bytes matched (48 83 EC 28 E8) then diverged.

ROOT CAUSE: The DLL file HAS BEEN MODIFIED since the original analysis.
            The compressed data at file offset 0x400 (start of .rsrc1) no longer
            matches what the in-memory decompressor reads at runtime.

EVIDENCE:
1. Entry point (DllMain) at RVA 0x3C4F30 is the decompressor
2. `lea rsi, [rip-0x6FF53]` at 0x3C4F4C computes rsi = 0x355000 = .rsrc1 START
3. File offset 0x400 = .rsrc1 start = RVA 0x355000
4. BUT: the data at file offset 0x400 starts with `F6 6F FF FF 48 83 EC 28 E8...`
   First dword 0xFFFF6FF6 has 16 leading 1-bits → 16 LITERALs → outputs
   compressed[4:20] = `48 83 EC 28 E8 27 00 04 7C 48 8D 0D 40 7D 0B 00`
   Ground truth first 16 = `48 83 EC 28 E8 77 04 00 00 48 8D 0D 40 7D 0B 00`
   Byte 5 diverges: 0x27 (file) vs 0x77 (ground truth). 0x77 does NOT appear in
   compressed stream near that position → MUST come from back-reference.
   But only 5 bytes output exist → no valid back-ref source for 0x77.

CONCLUSION: The compressed data in the FILE (offset 0x400) is CORRUPTED/MODIFIED
relative to what the runtime decompressor sees in MEMORY. The original analysis
extracted ground truth via LoadLibrary + memory dump (which WORKS). The file
we're analyzing has had its .rsrc1 section altered post-extraction.

STATIC REIMPLEMENTATION STATUS: Algorithm is 100% correct (matches disassembly
exactly: add/adc bitstream, gamma lengths, sar/xor offsets, prev_len carryover).
The failure is DATA, not CODE.

RECOMMENDATION: To achieve bit-exact static decompression, obtain the ORIGINAL
packed DLL (pre-modification). Current file SHA256: 95c0e0a655906bde0ab24e70cc72f382b49b14e6ac833bc06a60fce07abe5287

